Brutish dinosaurs are Slayer monsters that can be found in the northern area of Anachronia. They require level 99 Slayer to kill and are a type of dinosaur. Five of them can be found in the area.

Strategy[edit | edit source]

Brutish dinosaurs attack with strong melee attacks, thus it is recommended to use Protect or Deflect Melee when fighting them.

Every six auto-attacks, they will perform a special attack in which they will rear up on their hind legs and then lunge at their target, which can deal up to 2,757 damage. The damage of this attack is greatly reduced if using protection prayers, though it is advisable to use Resonance on this attack to help sustain lifepoints if needed. The Disruption Shield is another option if using melee or ranged.

Weapon poison and dreadnips are highly recommended when fighting due to their large number of lifepoints. Employing binds on them and attacking from a distance is also a good tactic to deal damage to them whilst preventing them from attacking.

They can be safe spotted by a plant on the west end of their area or the rock and cactus on the east side.

Alternatively, three of them can be attracted with a cannon in the right spot between the first and third dinosaur from the west, although this area is only three squares wide. Using Deflect Melee, an amulet of souls, and a scrimshaw of vampyrism, those three can be killed with high level melee weapons for high kill rates without needing food or movement.

Drops[edit | edit source]

Brutish dinosaurs roll two main drops per kill when on task.
